- WeeklySummaryPlugin in Models.swift
- Rules UI uses .id() modifier to prevent state leakage
- Bindings always look up current selection, not captured values

## Files to Check First
When making changes, these files are most commonly modified:
1. Models.swift - Data models, EventBus, plugins
2. AppModel.swift - Main application logic
3. RootView.swift - All UI views
4. DiscordService.swift - Discord API communication

## Critical Patterns to Maintain
- Always add .id() to detail views showing selected items
- Bindings must look up current state, not capture it
- Use MainActor for UI updates
- Document changes in CHANGELOG.md

